Read CLAUDE.md first — it is the authoritative brain for this repo.

Then read the engineering standards in .claude/rules/ (backend · frontend · scraping · security · devops · data-sources) and the CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md of the lane you're in (apps/web = frontend, repo root = backend, apps/scraper = scraping).

Three lanes, two seams — stay in your lane:
- Frontend (apps/web): React + TS + MUI + Tailwind PWA. Consume the API only via generated #[TypeScript] types — never hand-write a cross-API type.
- Backend (repo root): Laravel 11 modular (Controller → Data DTO → Action/Service → Repository → Job → Resource). Every endpoint guarded + rate-limited. Pydantic-style DTOs carry #[TypeScript].
- Scraping (apps/scraper): Python. Emit the NDJSON ingest contract to ./storage/ingest/normalized/; Laravel ingests it. Never touch the backend/DB.

Always:
- English in code, Bulgarian only in user-facing UI strings. No Cyrillic identifiers.
- Cyrillic data = UTF-8 (detect with chardet, decode cp1251 for legacy gov sites).
- No hardcoded strings (i18n). Only approved libraries; don't add a dependency without asking.
- Every flag links to a primary source (no source → no flag). Small diffs, run before "done".
